   SystemC Defects Repaired in 6.1
     * sccom crashed when linking in a design library with no SystemC objects.
     * In some cases, when the user does not name his instances, signals or
       ports explicitly SystemC crashed.
     * sccom no longer has a hard include of the current directory. If you need
       to include the current directory then a -I. option must be passed to
       sccom.
